      "writtenOn": "2015-09-30T19:48:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Moved to android/emulation/control/vm_operations.h\n\nSome thoughts:\n\n- The name-with-hyphens-style is qemu1 style really, so I\u0027ll keep that for qemu-vm-operations-etc. In AndroidEmu, c_files_use_underscore. Let\u0027s stick to that.\n\n- I like the idea of simply exposing a pointer for the qemu1 implementation. In fact, I\u0027ll add android/qemu-control-impl.h to expose _all_ control related pointers. \n\nI was unhappy adding a qemu-variant of all the interface headers I drop under android/emulation/control/ since they all just expose one pointer / function. They will still be implemented in separate qemu-specific-impl.c files since they have lots of static functions for the actual impl.",
      "parentUuid": "55eccecd_0d26d1f6",
      "revId": "1647f5e78af5d04af0b0ae39b9e3fa76cc082136",
